cs.cscollections.lists
Interface UnorderedListADT<T>

All Superinterfaces:
ListADT<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
UnorderedList
public interface UnorderedListADT<T>
extends ListADT<T>

The UnorderedListADT is an extension of the ListADT. It provides methods to allow elements to be inserted into a list. Resutling lists are unordered. The order of elements in the list correspond to the order the elements are inserted in the list.

Version:
v 1.0 3/2016

Method Detail

add

void add(T ele,
         int pos)

add inserts the specified element at the specified position in the list. The position must be in the range 0..size(). It is an error to try and insert an element out side this range. The new element becomes the element in the list that is in position pos. Note: add(ele, size()) has the same effect as addtoRear(ele).

Parameters:
ele - The element to insert.
pos - The position in the list at which to add the new element.
Throws:
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException

addAfter

void addAfter(T ele,
              T target)

addAfter inserts the specified element after the first occurance of target in the list. If the target is not found in the list an exception is raised.

Parameters:
ele - The element to insert.
target - The list element after which the insertion is to occur.
Throws:
ElementNotFoundException
